By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) said it has confirmed 180 new cases of #COVID-19 in the country. Releasing the report via it’s twitter handle late Wednesday night, the health agency said that Lagos State recorded 74 cases to come first on the table followed by Oyo with 41 cases. The FCT and Kaduna came third with 19 cases each. Others are Bauchi-12, Ogun-7,Rivers-4, Cross River and Edo-2 each. The new cases brought the total confirmed cases in Nigeria to 64,516 out of which60,737 had been discharged. It added that 1,162 deaths have been recorded since the index case was reported in February. See the table below which shows the state by state breakdown of total confirmed cases: By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The total confirmed cases of COVID-19 in Nigeria hit 59,001 as the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) reported 153 new fresh infections on Thursday. Similarly, the NCDC report released via it's twitter handle account further said that the total of 50, 452… October 2, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The latest report from the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has confirmed that the total confirmed cases of COVID-19 has risen risen to 56,388 with the 132 new infections reported on Monday night. This NCDC in report released via its twitter handle account… September 15, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The latest COVID-19 update from the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control revealed that 151 new cases were confirmed on Friday bringing total confirmed cases to 59,992. The report released via twitter handle account said that Lagos State, the epicentre for COVID-19 top the… October 10, 2020 In "Top Stories"